{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"We live on a human-dominated planet,"},{"time":3000,"text":"putting unprecedented pressure"},{"time":5000,"text":"on the systems on Earth."},{"time":7000,"text":"This is bad news, but perhaps surprising to you,"},{"time":9000,"text":"it's also part of the good news."},{"time":11000,"text":"We're the first generation -- thanks to science --"},{"time":14000,"text":"to be informed that we may be"},{"time":16000,"text":"undermining the stability and the ability"},{"time":18000,"text":"of planet Earth"},{"time":20000,"text":"to support human development as we know it."},{"time":22000,"text":"It's also good news, because the planetary risks we're facing"},{"time":25000,"text":"are so large,"},{"time":27000,"text":"that business as usual is not an option."},{"time":29000,"text":"In fact, we're in a phase"},{"time":31000,"text":"where transformative change is necessary,"},{"time":34000,"text":"which opens the window for innovation,"},{"time":36000,"text":"for new ideas and new paradigms."},{"time":39000,"text":"This is a scientific journey on the challenges facing humanity"},{"time":42000,"text":"in the global phase of sustainability."}]},{"cues":[{"time":44000,"text":"On this journey, I'd like to bring, apart from yourselves,"},{"time":47000,"text":"a good friend,"},{"time":49000,"text":"a stakeholder, who's always absent"},{"time":51000,"text":"when we deal with the negotiations on environmental issues,"},{"time":53000,"text":"a stakeholder who refuses to compromise --"},{"time":56000,"text":"planet Earth."},{"time":58000,"text":"So I thought I'd bring her with me today on stage,"},{"time":61000,"text":"to have her as a witness"},{"time":63000,"text":"of a remarkable journey,"},{"time":66000,"text":"which humbly reminds us"},{"time":68000,"text":"of the period of grace we've had"},{"time":70000,"text":"over the past 10,000 years."},{"time":72000,"text":"This is the living conditions on the planet over the last 100,000 years."},{"time":75000,"text":"It's a very important period --"},{"time":77000,"text":"it's roughly half the period when we've been fully modern humans on the planet."},{"time":80000,"text":"We've had the same, roughly, abilities"},{"time":82000,"text":"that developed civilizations as we know it."},{"time":84000,"text":"This is the environmental conditions on the planet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":86000,"text":"Here, used as a proxy, temperature variability."},{"time":89000,"text":"It was a jumpy ride. 80,000 years back in a crisis,"},{"time":92000,"text":"we leave Africa, we colonize Australia"},{"time":94000,"text":"in another crisis, 60,000 years back,"},{"time":96000,"text":"we leave Asia for Europe"},{"time":98000,"text":"in another crisis, 40,000 years back,"},{"time":100000,"text":"and then we enter"},{"time":102000,"text":"the remarkably stable Holocene phase,"},{"time":105000,"text":"the only period in the whole history of the planet,"},{"time":108000,"text":"that we know of, that can support human development."},{"time":110000,"text":"A thousand years into this period,"},{"time":112000,"text":"we abandon our hunting and gathering patterns."},{"time":115000,"text":"We go from a couple of million people"},{"time":117000,"text":"to the seven billion people we are today."},{"time":119000,"text":"The Mesopotamian culture: we invent agriculture,"},{"time":121000,"text":"we domesticate animals and plants."},{"time":123000,"text":"You have the Roman, the Greek and the story as you know it."},{"time":126000,"text":"The only phase, as we know it"},{"time":128000,"text":"that can support humanity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":130000,"text":"The trouble is we're putting a quadruple sqeeze"},{"time":132000,"text":"on this poor planet,"},{"time":134000,"text":"a quadruple sqeeze, which, as its first squeeze,"},{"time":137000,"text":"has population growth of course."},{"time":140000,"text":"Now, this is not only about numbers;"},{"time":142000,"text":"this is not only about the fact that we're seven billion people"},{"time":144000,"text":"committed to nine billion people, it's an equity issue as well."},{"time":147000,"text":"The majority of the environmental impacts on the planet"},{"time":149000,"text":"have been caused by the rich minority,"},{"time":151000,"text":"the 20 percent that jumped onto the industrial bandwagon"},{"time":153000,"text":"in the mid-18th century."},{"time":155000,"text":"The majority of the planet,"},{"time":157000,"text":"aspiring for development, having the right for development,"},{"time":159000,"text":"are in large aspiring for an unsustainable lifestyle,"},{"time":162000,"text":"a momentous pressure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":164000,"text":"The second pressure on the planet is, of course the climate agenda --"},{"time":166000,"text":"the big issue -- where the policy interpretation of science"},{"time":168000,"text":"is that it would be enough"},{"time":170000,"text":"to stabilize greenhouse gases at 450 ppm"},{"time":173000,"text":"to avoid average temperatures"},{"time":175000,"text":"exceeding two degrees,"},{"time":177000,"text":"to avoid the risk that we may be destabilizing"},{"time":179000,"text":"the West Antarctic Ice Sheet,"},{"time":181000,"text":"holding six meters -- level rising,"},{"time":183000,"text":"the risk of destabilizing the Greenland Ice Sheet,"},{"time":185000,"text":"holding another seven meters -- sea level rising."},{"time":187000,"text":"Now, you would have wished the climate pressure"},{"time":189000,"text":"to hit a strong planet, a resilient planet,"},{"time":191000,"text":"but unfortunately, the third pressure"},{"time":193000,"text":"is the ecosystem decline."},{"time":195000,"text":"Never have we seen, in the past 50 years,"},{"time":197000,"text":"such a sharp decline"},{"time":199000,"text":"of ecosystem functions and services on the planet,"},{"time":202000,"text":"one of them being the ability to regulate climate on the long term,"},{"time":205000,"text":"in our forests, land and biodiversity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":208000,"text":"The forth pressure is surprise,"},{"time":210000,"text":"the notion and the evidence"},{"time":212000,"text":"that we need to abandon our old paradigm,"},{"time":214000,"text":"that ecosystems behave linearly, predictably,"},{"time":217000,"text":"controllably in our -- so to say -- linear systems,"},{"time":220000,"text":"and that in fact, surprise is universal,"},{"time":222000,"text":"as systems tip over very rapidly, abruptly"},{"time":224000,"text":"and often irreversibly."},{"time":226000,"text":"This, dear friends, poses a human pressure on the planet"},{"time":229000,"text":"of momentous scale."},{"time":232000,"text":"We may, in fact, have entered a new geological era --"},{"time":235000,"text":"the Anthropocene,"},{"time":237000,"text":"where humans are the predominant driver of change"},{"time":239000,"text":"at a planetary level."}]},{"cues":[{"time":241000,"text":"Now, as a scientist,"},{"time":243000,"text":"what's the evidence for this?"},{"time":245000,"text":"Well, the evidence is,"},{"time":247000,"text":"unfortunately, ample."},{"time":249000,"text":"It's not only carbon dioxide"},{"time":251000,"text":"that has this hockey stick pattern of accelerated change."},{"time":254000,"text":"You can take virtually any parameter"},{"time":256000,"text":"that matters for human well-being --"},{"time":258000,"text":"nitrous oxide, methane,"},{"time":260000,"text":"deforestation, overfishing"},{"time":262000,"text":"land degredation, loss of species --"},{"time":265000,"text":"they all show the same pattern"},{"time":267000,"text":"over the past 200 years."},{"time":270000,"text":"Simultaneously, they branch off in the mid-50s,"},{"time":273000,"text":"10 years after the Second World War,"},{"time":276000,"text":"showing very clearly that the great acceleration of the human enterprise"},{"time":279000,"text":"starts in the mid-50s."},{"time":281000,"text":"You see, for the first time, an imprint on the global level."},{"time":284000,"text":"And I can tell you,"},{"time":286000,"text":"you enter the disciplinary research in each of these,"},{"time":288000,"text":"you find something remarkably important,"},{"time":291000,"text":"the conclusion that we may have come to the point"},{"time":294000,"text":"where we have to bend the curves,"},{"time":296000,"text":"that we may have entered the most challenging and exciting decade"},{"time":299000,"text":"in the history humanity on the planet,"},{"time":302000,"text":"the decade when we have to bend the curves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":305000,"text":"Now, as if this was not enough --"},{"time":307000,"text":"to just bend the curves and understanding the accelerated pressure on the planet --"},{"time":310000,"text":"we also have to recognize the fact"},{"time":312000,"text":"that systems do have multiple stable states,"},{"time":315000,"text":"separated by thresholds -- illustrated here by this ball and cup diagram,"},{"time":318000,"text":"where the depth of the cup is the resilience of the system."},{"time":321000,"text":"Now, the system may gradually --"},{"time":324000,"text":"under pressure of climate change,"},{"time":326000,"text":"erosion, biodiversity loss --"},{"time":328000,"text":"lose the depth of the cup, the resilience,"},{"time":330000,"text":"but appear to be healthy"},{"time":332000,"text":"and appear to suddenly, under a threshold,"},{"time":334000,"text":"be tipping over. Upff."},{"time":336000,"text":"Sorry. Changing state"},{"time":339000,"text":"and literally ending up"},{"time":341000,"text":"in an undesired situation,"},{"time":345000,"text":"where new biophysical logic takes over,"},{"time":348000,"text":"new species take over, and the system gets locked."}]},{"cues":[{"time":350000,"text":"Do we have evidence of this? Yes, coral reef systems."},{"time":354000,"text":"Biodiverse, low-nutrient, hard coral systems"},{"time":357000,"text":"under multiple pressures of overfishing,"},{"time":360000,"text":"unsustainable tourism, climate change."},{"time":362000,"text":"A trigger and the system tips over,"},{"time":364000,"text":"loses its resilience,"},{"time":366000,"text":"soft corals take over,"},{"time":368000,"text":"and we get undesired systems"},{"time":370000,"text":"that cannot support economic and social development."},{"time":372000,"text":"The Arctic -- a beautiful system --"},{"time":374000,"text":"a regulating biome at the planetary level,"},{"time":376000,"text":"taking the knock after knock on climate change,"},{"time":379000,"text":"appearing to be in a good state."},{"time":381000,"text":"No scientist could predict that in 2007,"},{"time":383000,"text":"suddenly, what could be crossing a threshold."},{"time":386000,"text":"The system suddenly, very surprisingly, loses 30 to 40 percent"},{"time":388000,"text":"of its summer ice cover."},{"time":390000,"text":"And the drama is, of course, that"},{"time":392000,"text":"when the system does this, the logic may change."},{"time":394000,"text":"It may get locked in an undesired state,"},{"time":396000,"text":"because it changes color, absorbs more energy,"},{"time":398000,"text":"and the system may get stuck."},{"time":400000,"text":"In my mind, the largest red flag warning for humanity"},{"time":403000,"text":"that we are in a precarious situation."},{"time":406000,"text":"As a sideline, you know that the only red flag that popped up here"},{"time":409000,"text":"was a submarine from an unnamed country"},{"time":411000,"text":"that planted a red flag at the bottom of the Arctic"},{"time":414000,"text":"to be able to control the oil resources."}]},{"cues":[{"time":417000,"text":"Now, if we have evidence, which we now have,"},{"time":420000,"text":"that wetlands, forests,"},{"time":422000,"text":"[unclear] monsoon system, the rainforests,"},{"time":424000,"text":"behave in this nonlinear way."},{"time":426000,"text":"30 or so scientists around the world"},{"time":428000,"text":"gathered and asked a question for the first time,"},{"time":430000,"text":"\"Do we have to put the planet into the the pot?\""},{"time":432000,"text":"So we have to ask ourselves:"},{"time":434000,"text":"are we threatening this extraordinarily stable Holocene state?"},{"time":438000,"text":"Are we in fact putting ourselves in a situation"},{"time":440000,"text":"where we're coming too close"},{"time":442000,"text":"to thresholds that could lead"},{"time":444000,"text":"to deleterious and very undesired,"},{"time":446000,"text":"if now catastrophic, change"},{"time":448000,"text":"for human development?"},{"time":450000,"text":"You know, you don't want to stand there."},{"time":452000,"text":"In fact, you're not even allowed to stand"},{"time":454000,"text":"where this gentleman is standing,"},{"time":456000,"text":"at the foaming, slippery waters at the threshold."},{"time":459000,"text":"In fact, there's a fence"},{"time":461000,"text":"quite upstream of this threshold,"},{"time":463000,"text":"beyond which you are in a danger zone."},{"time":465000,"text":"And this is the new paradigm,"},{"time":467000,"text":"which we gathered two, three years back,"},{"time":469000,"text":"recognizing that our old paradigm"},{"time":471000,"text":"of just analyzing and pushing and predicting"},{"time":473000,"text":"parameters into the future,"},{"time":475000,"text":"aiming at minimalizing environmental impacts, is of the past."}]},{"cues":[{"time":478000,"text":"Now we to ask ourselves:"},{"time":480000,"text":"which are the large environmental processes"},{"time":482000,"text":"that we have to be stewards of"},{"time":484000,"text":"to keep ourselves safe in the Holocene?"},{"time":486000,"text":"And could we even,"},{"time":488000,"text":"thanks to major advancements in Earth systems science,"},{"time":490000,"text":"identify the thresholds,"},{"time":492000,"text":"the points where we may expect nonlinear change?"},{"time":495000,"text":"And could we even define"},{"time":497000,"text":"a planetary boundary, a fence,"},{"time":500000,"text":"within which we then have a safe operating space for humanity?"},{"time":503000,"text":"This work, which was published in \"Nature,\""},{"time":505000,"text":"late 2009,"},{"time":507000,"text":"after a number of years of analysis,"},{"time":509000,"text":"led to the final proposition"},{"time":512000,"text":"that we can only find"},{"time":514000,"text":"nine planetary boundaries"},{"time":516000,"text":"with which, under active stewardship,"},{"time":519000,"text":"would allow ourselves to have a safe operating space."},{"time":522000,"text":"These include, of course, climate."},{"time":524000,"text":"It may surprise you that it's not only climate."},{"time":526000,"text":"But it shows that we are interconnected, among many systems on the planet,"},{"time":529000,"text":"with the three big systems, climate change,"},{"time":531000,"text":"stratospheric ozone depletion and ocean acidification"},{"time":534000,"text":"being the three big systems,"},{"time":536000,"text":"where the scientific evidence of large-scale thresholds"},{"time":539000,"text":"in the paleo-record of the history of the planet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":542000,"text":"But we also include, what we call, the slow variables,"},{"time":545000,"text":"the systems that, under the hood,"},{"time":547000,"text":"regulate and buffer the capacity of the resilience of the planet --"},{"time":550000,"text":"the interference of the big nitrogen and phosphorus cycles on the planet,"},{"time":553000,"text":"land use change, rate of biodiversity loss,"},{"time":555000,"text":"freshwater use,"},{"time":557000,"text":"functions which regulate"},{"time":560000,"text":"biomass on the planet, carbon sequestration, diversity."},{"time":563000,"text":"And then we have two parameters which we were not able to quantify --"},{"time":566000,"text":"air pollution,"},{"time":568000,"text":"including warming gases and air-polluting sulfates and nitrates,"},{"time":571000,"text":"but also chemical pollution."},{"time":574000,"text":"Together, these form an integrated whole"},{"time":577000,"text":"for guiding human development in the Anthropocene,"},{"time":579000,"text":"understanding that the planet"},{"time":581000,"text":"is a complex self-regulating system."},{"time":584000,"text":"In fact, most evidence indicates"},{"time":586000,"text":"that these nine may behave as three Musketeers,"},{"time":589000,"text":"\"One for all. All for one.\""},{"time":591000,"text":"You degrade forests, you go beyond the boundary on land,"},{"time":594000,"text":"you undermine the ability of the climate system"},{"time":596000,"text":"to stay stable."},{"time":598000,"text":"The drama here is, in fact, that"},{"time":600000,"text":"it may show that the climate challenge"},{"time":602000,"text":"is the easy one,"},{"time":604000,"text":"if you consider the whole challenge"},{"time":606000,"text":"of sustainable development."}]},{"cues":[{"time":609000,"text":"Now this is the Big Bang equivalent then of human development"},{"time":612000,"text":"within the safe operating space of the planetary boundaries."},{"time":614000,"text":"What you see here in black line is the safe operating space,"},{"time":617000,"text":"the quantified boundaries,"},{"time":619000,"text":"as suggested by this analysis."},{"time":621000,"text":"The yellow dot in the middle here is our starting point,"},{"time":623000,"text":"the pre-industrial point,"},{"time":625000,"text":"where we're very safely in the safe operating space."},{"time":627000,"text":"In the '50s, we start branching out."},{"time":630000,"text":"In the '60s already, through the green revolution"},{"time":632000,"text":"and the Haber-Bosch process"},{"time":634000,"text":"of fixing nitrogen from the atmosphere --"},{"time":636000,"text":"you know, human's today take out more nitrogen from the atmosphere"},{"time":639000,"text":"than the whole biosphere does naturally as a whole."},{"time":643000,"text":"We don't transgress the climate boundary until the early '90s,"},{"time":646000,"text":"actually, right after Rio."},{"time":648000,"text":"And today, we are in a situation where we estimate"},{"time":650000,"text":"that we've transgressed three boundaries,"},{"time":652000,"text":"the rate of biodiversity loss,"},{"time":654000,"text":"which is the sixth extinction period in the history of humanity --"},{"time":657000,"text":"one of them being the extinctions of the dinosaurs --"},{"time":660000,"text":"nitrogen and climate change."},{"time":662000,"text":"But we still have some degrees of freedom on the others,"},{"time":664000,"text":"but we are approaching fast"},{"time":666000,"text":"on land, water, phosphorus and oceans."},{"time":668000,"text":"But this gives a new paradigm"},{"time":670000,"text":"to guide humanity,"},{"time":672000,"text":"to put the light on our, so far"},{"time":675000,"text":"overpowered industrial vehicle,"},{"time":677000,"text":"which operates as if"},{"time":679000,"text":"we're only on a dark, straight highway."}]},{"cues":[{"time":682000,"text":"Now the question then is:"},{"time":684000,"text":"how gloomy is this?"},{"time":686000,"text":"Is then sustainable development utopia?"},{"time":688000,"text":"Well, there's no science to suggest."},{"time":690000,"text":"In fact, there is ample science"},{"time":692000,"text":"to indicate that we can do this transformative change,"},{"time":695000,"text":"that we have the ability"},{"time":697000,"text":"to now move into a new innovative,"},{"time":700000,"text":"a transformative gear,"},{"time":702000,"text":"across scales."},{"time":704000,"text":"The drama is, of course,"},{"time":706000,"text":"is that 200 countries on this planet"},{"time":708000,"text":"have to simultaneously start moving"},{"time":710000,"text":"in the same direction."},{"time":712000,"text":"But it changes fundamentally our governance and management paradigm,"},{"time":715000,"text":"from the current linear,"},{"time":717000,"text":"command and control thinking,"},{"time":719000,"text":"looking at efficiencies and optimization"},{"time":721000,"text":"towards a much more flexible,"},{"time":724000,"text":"a much more adaptive approach,"},{"time":726000,"text":"where we recognize that redundancy,"},{"time":728000,"text":"both in social and environmental systems,"},{"time":730000,"text":"is key to be able to deal"},{"time":732000,"text":"with a turbulent era of global change."},{"time":735000,"text":"We have to invest in persistence,"},{"time":737000,"text":"in the ability of social systems and ecological systems"},{"time":740000,"text":"to withstand shocks and still remain in that desired cup."},{"time":743000,"text":"We have to invest in transformations capability,"},{"time":746000,"text":"moving from crisis into innovation"},{"time":749000,"text":"and the ability to rise after a crisis,"},{"time":752000,"text":"and of course to adapt to unavoidable change."},{"time":754000,"text":"This is a new paradigm."},{"time":756000,"text":"We're not doing that at any scale on governance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":759000,"text":"But is it happening anywhere?"},{"time":761000,"text":"Do we have any examples of success"},{"time":763000,"text":"on this mind shift being applied at the local level?"},{"time":766000,"text":"Well, yes, in fact we do"},{"time":769000,"text":"and the list can start becoming longer and longer."},{"time":771000,"text":"There's good news here,"},{"time":773000,"text":"for example, from Latin America,"},{"time":775000,"text":"where plow-based farming systems"},{"time":778000,"text":"of the '50s and '60s"},{"time":780000,"text":"led farming basically to a dead-end,"},{"time":782000,"text":"with lower and lower yields, degrading the organic matter"},{"time":785000,"text":"and fundamental problems at the livelihood levels"},{"time":788000,"text":"in Paraguay, Uruguay and a number of countries, Brazil,"},{"time":791000,"text":"leading to innovation and entrepreneurship"},{"time":793000,"text":"among farmers in partnership with scientists"},{"time":795000,"text":"into an agricultural revolution of zero tillage systems"},{"time":798000,"text":"combined with mulch farming"},{"time":800000,"text":"with locally adapted technologies,"},{"time":802000,"text":"which today, for example, in some countries,"},{"time":805000,"text":"have led to a tremendous increase"},{"time":807000,"text":"in area under mulch, zero till farming"},{"time":810000,"text":"which, not only produces more food,"},{"time":812000,"text":"but also sequesters carbon."}]},{"cues":[{"time":814000,"text":"The Australian Great Barrier Reef is another success story."},{"time":817000,"text":"Under the realization from tourist operators,"},{"time":819000,"text":"fishermen,"},{"time":821000,"text":"the Australian Great Barrier Reef Authority and scientists"},{"time":824000,"text":"that the Great Barrier Reef is doomed"},{"time":826000,"text":"under the current governance regime."},{"time":829000,"text":"Global change, beautification rack culture,"},{"time":831000,"text":"overfishing and unsustainable tourism,"},{"time":833000,"text":"all together placing this system"},{"time":835000,"text":"in the realization of crisis."},{"time":837000,"text":"But the window of opportunity was innovation and new mindset,"},{"time":839000,"text":"which today has led to a completely new governance strategy"},{"time":842000,"text":"to build resilience,"},{"time":844000,"text":"acknowledge redundancy"},{"time":846000,"text":"and invest in the whole system as an integrated whole,"},{"time":849000,"text":"and then allow for much more redundancy in the system."}]},{"cues":[{"time":852000,"text":"Sweden, the country I come from, has other examples,"},{"time":855000,"text":"where wetlands in southern Sweden were seen as --"},{"time":858000,"text":"as in many countries -- as flood-prone polluted nuisance"},{"time":861000,"text":"in the peri-urban regions."},{"time":863000,"text":"But again, a crisis, new partnerships,"},{"time":866000,"text":"actors locally, transforming these"},{"time":868000,"text":"into a key component"},{"time":870000,"text":"of sustainable urban planning."},{"time":872000,"text":"So crisis leading into opportunities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":876000,"text":"Now, what about the future?"},{"time":878000,"text":"Well, the future, of course, has one massive challenge,"},{"time":881000,"text":"which is feeding a world of nine billion people."},{"time":883000,"text":"We need nothing less than a new green revolution,"},{"time":885000,"text":"and the planet boundaries shows"},{"time":887000,"text":"that agriculture has to go from a source of greenhouse gases to a sink."},{"time":890000,"text":"It has to basically do this on current land."},{"time":893000,"text":"We cannot expand anymore,"},{"time":895000,"text":"because it erodes the planetary boundaries."},{"time":897000,"text":"We cannot continue consuming water as we do today,"},{"time":900000,"text":"with 25 percent of world rivers not even reaching the ocean."},{"time":903000,"text":"And we need a transformation."},{"time":905000,"text":"Well, interestingly, and based on my work"},{"time":907000,"text":"and others in Africa, for example,"},{"time":909000,"text":"we've shown that even the most vulnerable small-scale rainfall farming systems,"},{"time":912000,"text":"with innovations and supplementary irrigation"},{"time":914000,"text":"to bridge dry spells and droughts,"},{"time":916000,"text":"sustainable sanitation systems to close the loop on nutrients"},{"time":919000,"text":"from toilets back to farmers' fields,"},{"time":922000,"text":"and innovations in tillage systems,"},{"time":924000,"text":"we can triple, quadruple, yield levels"},{"time":926000,"text":"on current land."}]},{"cues":[{"time":928000,"text":"Elinor Ostrom,"},{"time":930000,"text":"the latest Nobel laureate of economics,"},{"time":932000,"text":"clearly shows empirically across the world"},{"time":934000,"text":"that we can govern the commons"},{"time":936000,"text":"if we invest in trust,"},{"time":939000,"text":"local, action-based partnerships"},{"time":942000,"text":"and cross-scale institutional innovations,"},{"time":946000,"text":"where local actors,"},{"time":949000,"text":"together, can deal with the global commons"},{"time":951000,"text":"at a large scale."},{"time":953000,"text":"But even on the hard policy area we have innovations."},{"time":956000,"text":"We know that we have to move from our fossil dependence"},{"time":958000,"text":"very quickly into a low-carbon economy in record time."},{"time":961000,"text":"And what shall we do?"},{"time":963000,"text":"Everybody talks about carbon taxes -- it won't work -- emission schemes,"},{"time":966000,"text":"but for example, one policy measure,"},{"time":968000,"text":"feed-in tariffs on the energy system,"},{"time":970000,"text":"which is already applied,"},{"time":972000,"text":"from China doing it on offshore wind systems,"},{"time":974000,"text":"all the way to the U.S."},{"time":976000,"text":"where you give the guaranteed price for investment in renewable energy,"},{"time":978000,"text":"but you can subsidize electricity to poor people."},{"time":981000,"text":"You get people out of poverty."},{"time":983000,"text":"You solve the climate issue with regards to the energy sector,"},{"time":985000,"text":"while at the same time, stimulating innovation --"},{"time":988000,"text":"examples of things that can be out scaled quickly"},{"time":990000,"text":"at the planetary level."}]},{"cues":[{"time":992000,"text":"So there is -- no doubt -- opportunity here,"},{"time":994000,"text":"and we can list many, many examples"},{"time":997000,"text":"of transformative opportunities around the planet."},{"time":1000000,"text":"The key though in all of these,"},{"time":1002000,"text":"the red thread,"},{"time":1004000,"text":"is the shift in mindset,"},{"time":1006000,"text":"moving away from a situation where we simply are pushing ourselves"},{"time":1009000,"text":"into a dark future,"},{"time":1011000,"text":"where we instead backcast our future,"},{"time":1013000,"text":"and we say, \"What is the playing field on the planet?"},{"time":1016000,"text":"What are the planetary boundaries"},{"time":1018000,"text":"within which we can safely operate?\""},{"time":1020000,"text":"and then backtrack innovations within that."},{"time":1022000,"text":"But of course, the drama is, it clearly shows"},{"time":1024000,"text":"that incremental change is not an option."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1027000,"text":"So, there is scientific evidence."},{"time":1029000,"text":"They sort of say the harsh news,"},{"time":1031000,"text":"that we are facing the largest"},{"time":1033000,"text":"transformative development"},{"time":1035000,"text":"since the industrialization."},{"time":1037000,"text":"In fact, what we have to do over the next 40 years"},{"time":1039000,"text":"is much more dramatic and more exciting"},{"time":1042000,"text":"than what we did when we moved into"},{"time":1045000,"text":"the situation we're in today."},{"time":1047000,"text":"Now, science indicates that,"},{"time":1049000,"text":"yes, we can achieve a prosperous future"},{"time":1051000,"text":"within the safe operating space,"},{"time":1053000,"text":"if we move simultaneously,"},{"time":1055000,"text":"collaborating on a global level, from local to global scale,"},{"time":1058000,"text":"in transformative options, which build resilience on a finite planet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1061000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1063000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}